	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>When you swear an oath as a paragon, you begin a life in service to your chosen ideals or virtues. Many paladins who become paragons choose to live their lives as virtuously as possible. Some paladins choose a specific virtue or code of honor, and they often hold themselves to almost impossibly high standards. Paragons are more resistant to mental influence than other paladins, and can stand as literal beacons of light against their foes.</em></p><table><caption><p>The Paragon</p></caption><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\"><p>Level</p></th><th scope=\"col\"><p>Features</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.eEEEvZIs5DK6LLic]{Inspiring Light} or @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.1h1j8h29V9gDtlMD]{Sacred Weapon}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.uBu2SZwTE3OR9C7g]{Aura of Devotion}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.eEEEvZIs5DK6LLic]{Inspiring Light} or @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.1h1j8h29V9gDtlMD]{Sacred Weapon}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.kq6N82rDpcrZUqWx]{Purity of Body} or @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.MPmGkNteGluUD5Ih]{Purity of Spirit}</p></td></tr></tbody></table><table><caption><p>Expanded Spell List</p></caption><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\"><p>Paladin Level</p></th><th scope=\"col\"><p>Extra Spells</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p>3</p></td><td><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.pw27A83p6TFHAzim]{Sanctuary}</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5</p></td><td><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.gQCBKxTyZeqCvy0D]{Lesser Restoration}</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>9</p></td><td><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.Y9ujzi4f01yflTyj]{Beacon of Hope}</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>13</p></td><